<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The declaration declares a const pointer to a mutable OS_common_record_t: 'extern OS_common_record_t *const OS_global_timebase_table'. MISRA R8.13 requires pointers to point to const-qualified types whenever possible. In OS_TimeBaseGetInfo the table is only read (record->name_entry, record->creator, etc.), so the pointee could be const. The declaration should be 'extern const OS_common_record_t *const OS_global_timebase_table' (or at least 'const OS_common_record_t *') if the table contents are not modified elsewhere. As written the pointer does not point to a const-qualified type, so the rule is violated.
</scenario>
