explanation:
Not correct. MISRA R8.13 advises that pointers should point to const-qualified types when that is possible for the overall program, but you cannot decide that from a single read-only use-site. The declaration shown is
  extern OS_common_record_t *const OS_global_timebase_table;
which is a const pointer to mutable records. The fact that OS_TimeBaseGetInfo only reads the table does not by itself require the global pointee type to be const — the pointee must remain non-const if other parts of the code must modify those records. The additional snippets show a non-const OS_timebase_table array (and the general object table design implies entries are created/modified elsewhere), so marking the pointee const would likely be incorrect for the whole program. Therefore the agent A’s claim that this is a MISRA 8.13 violation is not justified based on the provided code.
